<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef9f7a64-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302905"><num value="302905">§ 302905.</num><heading> Religious property</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idef9f7a65-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302905/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">In General</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>Grants may be made under this chapter for the preservation, stabilization, restoration, or rehabilitation of religious property listed on the National Register if the purpose of the grant—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9f7a66-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302905/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> is secular;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9f7a67-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302905/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> does not promote religion; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idef9f7a68-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302905/a/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> seeks to protect qualities that are historically significant.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idef9f7a69-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s302905/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Effect of Section</inline>.—</heading><content>Nothing in this section shall be construed to authorize the use of any funds made available under this subdivision for the acquisition of any religious property listed on the National Register.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idef9f7a6a-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/287/s3">Pub. L. 113–287, § 3</ref>, <date date="2014-12-19">Dec. 19, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/3204">128 Stat. 3204</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
